Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art, taken at an angle, showing figures of at least two boats, three unidentified quadrupeds and several unidentified shapes. Largest figure is that at right of unidentified quadruped, schematic, pecked in outline, upright and facing right ,with unidentified incised vertical shape to right. To lower left of this is schematic, faint pecked figure, either of cow with extremely outsized horns pointing up towards larger figure or of unidentified animal standing below an unidentified arc shape (boat?). Further large arc is at lower centre. Largest arc is in foreground at left, showing boat, with unidentified schematic quadruped and further boat with oars pointing up below it. To left of image are at least eight human figures apparently fighting each other in groups of two. Many are holding clubs/bows(?) in their hands. A 10cm scale has been fitted at the bottom of the image. Eastern Desert, Egypt Scanned
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
